==English==

===Etymology===
From the [[w:Portuguese language|Portuguese]] ''[[inhame]]'' and [[w:Spanish language|Spanish]] ''[[ñame]]'', possibly from the [[w:Fulani language|Fulani]] ''[[nyami]]'', (“to [[eat]]”). The term was coined in [[w:1657|1657]].

===Noun===
'''yam''' (plural: [[yams]])
{{wikipedia}}
# the edible, starchy, [[tuberous]] root of any climbing vine of the genus ''[[Dioscorea]]'', usually cultivated in the Eastern and Western hemispheres
# {{italbrac|Southern U.S.}} A [[sweet potato]]
# {{italbrac|Scottish}} [[potato]]


